{{Infobox building | name = 900 West Randolph | alternate_names = | building_type = | architectural_style = | classification = | location = | address = | location_city = [[Chicago]] | location_country = | est_completion = | topped_out_date = | completion_date = | closing_date = | cost = | height = | architectural = | tip = | antenna_spire = | material = | size = | floor_area = | architect = [[Morris Adjmi]] }} '''900 West Randolph''' is proposed skyscraper in [[Chicago]] designed by architectural firm Morris Adjmi. As proposed, the building will contain residences. It is one of two buildings proposed by developer [[Related Companies|Related Midwest]] in the [[West Loop]] opposed by local residents due to their height. The other is [[725 West Randolph]].
Adjmi took cues from the infrastructure of Chicago in designing the building.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicago.curbed.com/2018/1/31/16952236/west-loop-condo-tower-development-adjmi|title=Morris Adjmi's 51-story Fulton Market condo tower makes its public debut|last=Koziarz|first=Jay|date=31 January 2018|publisher=Curbed|accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>
