:''For other places with the same name, see [[Ağasıbəyli (disambiguation)]].'' {{coord|41|08|N|49|07|E|display=title}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name =Agasibeyli |native_name = |pushpin_map =Azerbaijan |pushpin_mapsize =300 |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|Azerbaijan}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|Rayon]] |subdivision_name1 =[[Siazan Rayon|Siazan]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = |population_total = |population_density_km2 = |timezone =[[Azerbaijan Time|AZT]] |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST =[[Azerbaijan Time|AZT]] |utc_offset_DST = +5 |coordinates = {{coord|41|08|N|49|07|E|region:AZ|display=inline}} |elevation_m = |area_code = |website = }} '''Agasibeyli''' (also, '''Agasi-Bek-Obasi''') is a village in the [[Siazan Rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]].
== Toponymic explanation ==
'''Aghasibeyli''' – village in Vedibasar area, [[Iravan Khanate|Iravan khanate]]. Local pronunciation form is as Aghasli. In 1828-1832 the [[Azerbaijanian]] population was expatriated and the village was ruined. In 1926 the village was settled by Kurds and [[Armenians]]. In the 1940s the village was liquidated. Aghasibeyli is the name of a tribe who founded the village.<ref> B.A. Budagov, G.A. Geybullayev. Explanatory Dictionary of Azerbaijani Origin Places’ Names.</ref>
==See also== * [[Western Azerbaijan]] * [[Iravan Khanate]]
== Literature == * Петрушевский И.П. Очерки по истории феодальных отношений Азербайджана и Армении в XVI - начале XIX вв. Л., 1949. * Azərbaycanın izahlı coğrafi adlar luğəti. Bakı, 1960. ==References== {{reflist}} *{{GEOnet2|32FA8815230F3774E0440003BA962ED3}}
