This is a list of flags used in the '''[[Luxembourg|Grand Duchy of Luxembourg]]''', a country in western [[Europe]]. For more information about the national flag, visit the article '''[[Flag of Luxembourg]]'''. ==National flag==
{| border="2" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;" |- bgcolor="#efefef" ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="300"|Use!!width="300"|Description |- | [[File:Flag of Luxembourg.svg |100px|border]] || 1848 - || [[Flag of Luxembourg]] (Ratio: 3:5) || The flag is a horizontal tricolor of red, white, and blue in 1848, but it was not officially adopted until 1972. |- | [[File:Flag of Luxembourg wide.svg|100px|border]] || 1848 - || Flag of Luxembourg (Ratio: 1:2) || The national flag in 1:2 ratio. |- |}
==Ensign==
{| border="2" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;" |- bgcolor="#efefef" ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="300"|Use!!width="300"|Description |- | [[File:Civil Ensign of Luxembourg.svg|100px|border]] || 1972 - || [[Civil Ensign]] and [[Civil Air Ensign]] of Luxembourg || A [[banner of arms|banner]] of the [[coat of arms of Luxembourg]]. It is made of ten horizontal white and blue stripes with a red lion with yellow claws, teeth, tongue and crown over all. |}
==Standard of the Grand Duke==
{| border="2" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;" |- bgcolor="#efefef" ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="300"|Use!!width="300"|Description |- | [[File:Grand ducal standard of Luxembourg.svg|100px|border]] || 2001 - || [[Royal Standard|Standard]] of the [[Grand Duke of Luxembourg|Grand Duke]] || An orange flag with the middle coat of arms of the Grand Duke. |- |}
